When a polynomial is divided by $-3x^5 + 10x - 11,$ what are the possible degrees of the remainder?  Enter all the possible values, separated by commas.
inference:
The degree of the remainder is always less than the degree of the divisor. In this case, the degree of the divisor is 5, so the degree of the remainder can be 0, 1, 2, 3, or 4.

Final Answer: \boxed{$0, 1, 2, 3, 4$}. I hope it is correct.
ground_truth: In general, when a polynomial is divided by a polynomial of degree $d,$ then the possible degrees of the remainder are 0, 1, 2, $\dots,$ $d - 1.$  Therefore, the possible degrees of the remainder here are $\boxed{0,1,2,3,4}.$
